cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.SD, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for matrix-vector multiplication, which is a fundamental numerical computation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper introduces a new notion of recurrence width for matrices and designs algorithms based on this notion. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as the paper mentions orthogonal polynomial transforms, which are used in geometric modeling and computer graphics. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a possibility as the paper mentions Discrete Cosine/Sine Transforms, which are used in audio and image compression. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is a possibility as the paper mentions applications in multipoint evaluations of multivariate polynomials.
